# Backend Go Rules

## Layers

- `internal/domain` ‚Äî pure types and repository interfaces; no imports from adapter/usecase.
- `internal/usecase` ‚Äî business logic; depends only on domain + infrastructure interfaces injected via struct fields.
- `internal/adapter/http/controller` ‚Äî parse JSON, call usecase, write response; Swagger godoc on handlers.
- `internal/adapter/persistence/postgres` ‚Äî SQL via pgx; implement `domain/repository` interfaces.

## HTTP patterns

- Routes registered in `internal/adapter/http/router.go` using Go 1.22+ `mux.HandleFunc("METHOD /path", ...)`.
- JSON helpers: `httpx.WriteJSON`, `httpx.WriteError`.
- Auth: `middleware.Auth.RequireAPI` reads `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.
- Presenters map `entity.User` ‚Üí `response.User` (never expose domain entities in JSON).

## Errors

- Usecase sentinel errors: `ErrInvalidCredentials`, `ErrInvalidResetToken`, `ErrUsernameTaken`, etc.
- Controllers map errors to HTTP status in `switch` blocks (400/403/409).
- Wrap internal errors with `fmt.Errorf("context: %w", err)`.

## Swagger

- Annotate handlers with `// @Summary`, `@Router`, `@Param`, `@Success`, `@Failure`.
- Regenerate: `cd google-auth-standalone && make swagger`.

## Migrations

- SQL pairs in `db/migrations/*.up.sql` / `*.down.sql`.
- Create via `scripts/create-migration.sh "name"`.
- Applied on server start and via `make migrate`; tracked in `"AUTH".schema_migrations`.

## Testing

- Table-driven `*_test.go` in same package or `_test` package for usecases.
- Run: `go test ./...` from `google-auth-standalone/`.
